00:18:06,861 --> 00:18:09,097
Wh-What's wrong?

242
00:18:09,197 --> 00:18:11,019
I-I thought you
like frog's breath.

243
00:18:11,117 --> 00:18:14,695
Nothing's more suspicious
than frog's breath.

244
00:18:14,797 --> 00:18:19,499
Until you taste it,
I won't swallow a spoonful.

245
00:18:19,597 --> 00:18:22,314
I'm not hungry.
Oops.

246
00:18:22,413 --> 00:18:25,729
You want me to starve.

247
00:18:25,838 --> 00:18:30,475
An old man like me,
who hardly has strength as it is.

248
00:18:30,573 --> 00:18:34,218
Me, to whom you owe
your very life.

249
00:18:34,317 --> 00:18:37,034
Oh, don't be silly.

250
00:18:37,133 --> 00:18:41,061
Mmm! See?

251
00:18:41,165 --> 00:18:43,020
Scrumptious!

252
00:18:51,117 --> 00:18:54,532
Did anyone think
to dredge the lake?

253
00:18:54,638 --> 00:18:56,874
This morning.

254
00:18:58,893 --> 00:19:02,438
- Hear that? Shh.
- What?

255
00:19:02,541 --> 00:19:05,061
Zero!

256
00:19:08,237 --> 00:19:10,059
Jack's back!

257
00:19:10,157 --> 00:19:11,979
Yea!
Jack's back!

258
00:19:19,598 --> 00:19:21,540
Where have you been?

259
00:19:21,645 --> 00:19:24,994
Call a town meeting
and I'll tell everyone all about it!

260
00:19:25,101 --> 00:19:27,949
- When?
- Immediately!

261
00:19:31,757 --> 00:19:37,256
Town meeting!
Town meeting!

262
00:19:37,357 --> 00:19:39,812
Town meeting tonight!

263
00:19:41,101 --> 00:19:44,135
Town meeting!

264
00:19:44,237 --> 00:19:47,139
Town meeting
tonight!

265
00:20:03,917 --> 00:20:06,372
Listen, everyone.

266
00:20:06,477 --> 00:20:10,634
I want to tell you
about Christmas Town.

267
00:20:13,358 --> 00:20:15,180
# There were objects #
# so peculiar #

268
00:20:15,278 --> 00:20:17,100
# They were not #
# to be believed #

269
00:20:17,198 --> 00:20:19,816
# All around things #
# to tantalize my brain #

270
00:20:19,917 --> 00:20:23,594
# It's a world unlike #
# anything I've ever seen #

271
00:20:23,693 --> 00:20:26,857
# And as hard as I tried #
# I can't seem to describe #

272
00:20:26,957 --> 00:20:30,055
# Like a most #
# improbable dream #

273
00:20:30,157 --> 00:20:33,572
# But you must believe #
# when I tell you this #

274
00:20:33,677 --> 00:20:38,859
# It's as real as my skull #
# and it does exist #

275
00:20:38,957 --> 00:20:41,062
Here, let me show you.

276
00:20:42,765 --> 00:20:45,798
Ooh!

277
00:20:45,901 --> 00:20:48,290
# This is a thing #
# called a present #

278
00:20:48,397 --> 00:20:51,080
- # The whole thing starts with a box #
- # A box #

279
00:20:51,181 --> 00:20:52,774
- # Is it steel #
- # Are there locks #

280
00:20:52,877 --> 00:20:56,106
- # Is it filled with a pox #
- # A pox How delightful, a pox #

281
00:20:56,205 --> 00:20:57,895
If you please.

282
00:20:57,997 --> 00:20:59,819
# Just a box with #
# bright colored paper #

283
00:20:59,917 --> 00:21:02,535
# And the whole thing's #
# topped with a bow #

284
00:21:02,637 --> 00:21:03,979
- # A bow #
- # But why #

285
00:21:04,077 --> 00:21:05,736
- # How ugly! What's in it #
- # What's in it #

286
00:21:05,837 --> 00:21:07,463
# That's the point of the thing #
# Not to know #

287
00:21:07,565 --> 00:21:08,776
- # It's a bat #
- # Will it bend #

288
00:21:08,877 --> 00:21:10,219
- # It's a rat #
- # Will it break #

289
00:21:10,317 --> 00:21:12,772
# Perhaps it's the head #
# that I found in the lake #

290
00:21:12,878 --> 00:21:15,333
# Listen now #
# You don't understand #

291
00:21:15,437 --> 00:21:18,536
# That's not the point #
# of Christmasland #

292
00:21:18,638 --> 00:21:20,460
# Now pay attention #

293
00:21:20,558 --> 00:21:22,663
# We pick up #
# an oversized sock #

294
00:21:22,765 --> 00:21:25,100
# And hang it like this #
# on the wall #

295
00:21:25,197 --> 00:21:27,020
# Oh, yes, does it #
# still have a foot #

296
00:21:27,117 --> 00:21:30,216
# Let me see, let me look #
# Is it rotted and covered with gook #

297
00:21:30,317 --> 00:21:32,139
Um, let me explain.

298
00:21:32,237 --> 00:21:34,538
# There's no foot inside #
# but there's candy #

299
00:21:34,637 --> 00:21:36,612
# Or sometimes it's filled #
# with small toys #

300
00:21:36,717 --> 00:21:39,467
- # Small toys, do they bite #
# or explode in the sack #
- # Do they snap #

301
00:21:39,565 --> 00:21:42,053
# Perhaps they just spring out #
# and scare girls and boys #

302
00:21:42,157 --> 00:21:44,612
# What a splendid idea #
# This Christmas sounds fun #

303
00:21:44,717 --> 00:21:47,750
# I fully endorse it #
# Let's try it at once #

304
00:21:47,853 --> 00:21:49,740
# Everyone, please #
# Now not so fast #

305
00:21:49,837 --> 00:21:52,871
# There's something here #
# that you don't quite grasp #

306
00:21:52,973 --> 00:21:55,177
I don't know.
Do you get it?

307
00:21:55,277 --> 00:21:58,375
Well, I may as well
give them what they want.

308
00:21:58,477 --> 00:22:01,892
# And the best I must confess #
# I have saved for the last #

309
00:22:01,997 --> 00:22:05,258
# For the ruler #
# of this Christmasland #

310
00:22:05,357 --> 00:22:08,619
# Is a fearsome king #
# with a deep, mighty voice #

311
00:22:08,717 --> 00:22:11,978
# Least, that's what #
# I've come to understand #

312
00:22:12,077 --> 00:22:15,339
# And I've also heard it told #
# that he's something to behold #

313
00:22:15,437 --> 00:22:18,535
# Like a lobster #
# Huge and red #

314
00:22:18,637 --> 00:22:22,052
# When he sets out to slay #
# with his rain gear on #

315
00:22:22,157 --> 00:22:25,418
# Carting bulging sacks #
# with his big, great arms #

316
00:22:25,517 --> 00:22:28,779
# That is, #
# so I've heard it said #

317
00:22:28,877 --> 00:22:32,292
# And on a dark, cold night #
# Under full moonlight #

318
00:22:32,397 --> 00:22:37,733
# He flies into a fog like #
# a vulture in the sky #

319
00:22:37,837 --> 00:22:40,936
# And they call him #

320
00:22:41,037 --> 00:22:47,082
# Sandy Claws #

321
00:22:49,485 --> 00:22:52,452
# Well, at least #
# they're excited #

322
00:22:52,557 --> 00:22:55,078
# But they don't #
# understand #

323
00:22:55,181 --> 00:22:57,004
# That special kind #
# of feeling #

324
00:22:57,101 --> 00:22:59,654
# In Christmasland #

325
00:22:59,757 --> 00:23:02,059
Oh, well.

326
00:23:11,597 --> 00:23:13,419
Hmm.

327
00:23:20,717 --> 00:23:22,539
Hmm.

328
00:23:33,741 --> 00:23:38,378
There's got to be a logical way
to explain this Christmas thing.

329
00:23:49,037 --> 00:23:54,372
You've poisoned me for the last time,
you wretched girl.

330
00:24:02,637 --> 00:24:05,899
Oh, my head!

331
00:24:08,717 --> 00:24:11,651
The door is open!

332
00:24:11,757 --> 00:24:15,106
- Hello?
- Jack Skellington!

333
00:24:15,213 --> 00:24:17,515
Up here, my boy.

334
00:24:17,613 --> 00:24:20,777
Doctor, I need to borrow
some equipment.

335
00:24:20,877 --> 00:24:23,430
Is that so?
Whatever for?

336
00:24:23,533 --> 00:24:27,494
I'm conducting a series
of experiments.

337
00:24:27,597 --> 00:24:30,696
How perfectly
marvelous.

338
00:24:30,797 --> 00:24:34,691
- Curiosity killed the cat, you know.
- I know.

339
00:24:34,797 --> 00:24:38,953
Come on into the lab
and we'll get you all fixed up.

340
00:24:39,053 --> 00:24:41,541
Hmm.
Experiments?

341
00:24:44,717 --> 00:24:46,889
Zero, I'm home.

342
00:25:48,717 --> 00:25:51,019
Interesting reaction.

343
00:25:51,117 --> 00:25:53,092
But what does it mean?

344
00:27:28,205 --> 00:27:33,256
You can come out now
if you promise to behave.

345
00:27:33,357 --> 00:27:35,332
Sally?

346
00:27:35,437 --> 00:27:37,259
Sally?

347
00:27:37,357 --> 00:27:41,132
Oh! Gone again!

348
00:27:53,837 --> 00:27:55,659
Hmm.

349
00:28:41,517 --> 00:28:43,819
Oh!

350
00:29:05,581 --> 00:29:08,451
# Something's up with Jack #
# Something's up with Jack #

351
00:29:11,117 --> 00:29:14,051
# Don't know if we're ever #
# going to get him back #

352
00:29:16,110 --> 00:29:19,176
# He's all alone up there #
# Locked away inside #

353
00:29:21,518 --> 00:29:23,819
- # Never says a word #
- # Hope he hasn't died #

354
00:29:23,917 --> 00:29:27,081
# Something's up with Jack #
# Something's up with Jack #

355
00:29:34,797 --> 00:29:37,732
# Christmastime #
# is buzzing in my skull #

356
00:29:37,838 --> 00:29:40,772
# Will it let me be #
# I cannot tell #

357
00:29:40,877 --> 00:29:43,811
# There's so many things #
# I cannot grasp #

358
00:29:43,917 --> 00:29:46,852
# When I think I've got it #
# then at last #

359
00:29:46,957 --> 00:29:49,892
# Through my bony fingers #
# it does slip #

360
00:29:49,997 --> 00:29:51,939
# Like a snowflake #
# in a fiery grip #

361
00:29:52,045 --> 00:29:55,787
# Something here I'm not quite getting, #
# though I try I keep forgetting #

362
00:29:55,885 --> 00:29:59,497
# Like a memory #
# long since past #

363
00:29:59,597 --> 00:30:01,419
# Here in an instant #
# Gone in a flash #

364
00:30:01,517 --> 00:30:04,452
# What does it mean #
# What does it mean #

365
00:30:04,557 --> 00:30:06,216
# In these little #
# bric-a-brac #

366
00:30:06,317 --> 00:30:07,975
# A secret's waiting #
# to be cracked #

367
00:30:08,077 --> 00:30:09,899
# These dolls and toys #
# confuse me so #

368
00:30:09,997 --> 00:30:12,299
# Confound it all #
# I love it though #

369
00:30:12,398 --> 00:30:14,220
# Simple objects #
# Nothing more #

370
00:30:14,318 --> 00:30:16,140
# But something's hidden #
# through a door #

371
00:30:16,238 --> 00:30:19,499
# Though I do not #
# have the key #

372
00:30:19,597 --> 00:30:21,255
# Something's here #
# I cannot see #

373
00:30:21,357 --> 00:30:23,812
# What does it mean #
# What does it mean #

374
00:30:24,973 --> 00:30:26,632
# What does it mean #

375
00:30:26,733 --> 00:30:31,654
Hmm. Hmm.

376
00:30:31,757 --> 00:30:34,212
# I've read these Christmas #
# books so many times #

377
00:30:34,317 --> 00:30:37,416
# I know the stories #
# and I know the rhymes #

378
00:30:37,517 --> 00:30:40,451
# I know the Christmas carols #
# all by heart #

379
00:30:40,557 --> 00:30:43,492
# My skull's so full #
# It's tearing me apart #

380
00:30:43,597 --> 00:30:46,379
# As often as I've read them #
# something's wrong #

381
00:30:46,477 --> 00:30:49,511
# So hard to put #
# my bony finger on #

382
00:30:49,613 --> 00:30:52,777
# Or perhaps it's really not as deep #
# as I've been led to think #

383
00:30:52,877 --> 00:30:56,138
# Am I trying #
# much too hard #

384
00:30:56,237 --> 00:30:58,059
# Of course, I've been #
# too close to see #

385
00:30:58,157 --> 00:31:01,256
# The answer's right in front of me #
# Right in front of me #

386
00:31:01,358 --> 00:31:03,180
# It's simple really #
# Very clear #

387
00:31:03,278 --> 00:31:05,100
# Like music drifting #
# in the air #

388
00:31:05,198 --> 00:31:08,231
# Invisible #
# but everywhere #

389
00:31:08,333 --> 00:31:10,155
# Just because #
# I cannot see it #

390
00:31:10,253 --> 00:31:12,075
# Doesn't mean #
# I can't believe it #

391
00:31:12,173 --> 00:31:16,133
# You know I think this Christmas thing #
# is not as tricky as it seems #

392
00:31:16,237 --> 00:31:19,499
# And why should they have all the fun #
# It should belong to anyone #

393
00:31:19,598 --> 00:31:21,420
# Not anyone, in fact #
# but me #

394
00:31:21,518 --> 00:31:23,176
# Why, I can make #
# a Christmas tree #

395
00:31:23,277 --> 00:31:24,619
# And there's no reason #
# I can find #

396
00:31:24,717 --> 00:31:26,539
# I couldn't handle #
# Christmastime #

397
00:31:26,637 --> 00:31:28,295
# I bet I could #
# improve it too #

398
00:31:28,397 --> 00:31:31,658
# And that's exactly #
# what I'll do #

399
00:31:31,757 --> 00:31:33,645
Hee-hee-hee-hee-hee!

400
00:31:33,741 --> 00:31:35,978
Eureka!

401
00:31:36,077 --> 00:31:40,681
This year...
Christmas will be ours!

402
00:31:44,621 --> 00:31:46,693
Patience, everyone.

403
00:31:46,797 --> 00:31:50,375
Jack has a special job
for each of us.

404
00:31:51,757 --> 00:31:55,019
Dr. Finkelstein!

405
00:31:55,118 --> 00:31:57,736
Your Christmas
assignment is ready.

406
00:32:00,397 --> 00:32:04,456
Dr. Finkelstein, to
the front of the line.

407
00:32:08,173 --> 00:32:11,337
What kind of noise is that
for a baby to make?

408
00:32:11,438 --> 00:32:14,220
- Perhaps it can be improved?
- No problem.

409
00:32:14,318 --> 00:32:16,140
I knew it!

410
00:32:16,238 --> 00:32:18,791
Doctor!
Thank you for coming.

411
00:32:18,893 --> 00:32:21,479
We need
some of these.

412
00:32:21,581 --> 00:32:23,818
Hmm.

413
00:32:23,918 --> 00:32:27,747
Their construction
should be exceedingly simple, I think.

414
00:32:27,853 --> 00:32:31,017
How horrible
our Christmas will be.

415
00:32:31,117 --> 00:32:33,703
No!
How jolly!

416
00:32:33,805 --> 00:32:37,417
Oh. How jolly
our Christmas will be.

417
00:32:40,397 --> 00:32:43,015
- What are you doing here?
- Jack sent for us.

418
00:32:43,118 --> 00:32:45,092
- Specifically.
- By name.

419
00:32:45,197 --> 00:32:47,946
- Lock.
- Shock.
- Barrel.

420
00:32:48,045 --> 00:32:49,900
Jack!
Jack!

421
00:32:49,997 --> 00:32:51,884
It's Boogie's boys.

422
00:32:51,981 --> 00:32:56,137
Ah, Halloween's finest
trick-or-treaters.

423
00:32:56,237 --> 00:32:59,499
The job I have for you
is top secret.

424
00:32:59,597 --> 00:33:02,444
It requires craft,
cunning, mischief.

425
00:33:02,541 --> 00:33:05,258
And we thought you
didn't like us, Jack.

426
00:33:07,341 --> 00:33:10,537
Absolutely no one is to know about it.
Not a soul!

427
00:33:10,637 --> 00:33:12,906
Now...

428
00:33:13,005 --> 00:33:17,740
...tree...

429
00:33:17,837 --> 00:33:20,138
...Christmas Town...

430
00:33:20,237 --> 00:33:23,718
Ow! Hmm.

431
00:33:23,821 --> 00:33:25,894
And one more thing.

432
00:33:25,997 --> 00:33:29,575
Leave that no-account
Oogie Boogie out of this!

433
00:33:29,677 --> 00:33:31,237
Whatever you say, Jack.

434
00:33:31,341 --> 00:33:33,829
- Of course, Jack.
- Wouldn't dream of it, Jack.

435
00:33:52,877 --> 00:33:55,659
